  "market_context": "Uptrend on NQ1! 2-minute chart on 1/12/2023; price made higher highs, with a propulsion block formed off a prior bullish order block. Analyst identified an inversion after price closed over the fair value gap created at the propulsion block.",
  "key_observation": "After sweeping sell-side liquidity and forming a fair value gap at a propulsion block, price closed over the gap—creating an inversion that served as a high-probability long entry zone for trend continuation.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Analyst observed an uptrend with a higher high, then identified a propulsion block (order block formed off another order block) near 15890–15905.",
    "Step 2: Noted that price retraced to the propulsion block and created a fair value gap (FVG) during the pullback.",
    "Step 3: Waited for price to close over the FVG, confirming it as an inversion (IFVG), which then acted as support.",
    "Step 4: Took a long entry near the consequent encroachment (CE) of the inverted FVG, with stop below the swing low (15864), targeting the other side of the range (15963.5–15990).",
    "Step 5: Price respected the inversion, swept liquidity once more, displaced upward, and made a new higher high—validating the setup."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade executed long at inversion (CE of IFVG), stop at 15864, target at 15963.5–15990; price reached new high, confirming successful trend continuation.",
  "lessons": "In an established uptrend, inversions at propulsion blocks or old FVGs provide high-probability entries when price closes over the gap. Always require a close over the FVG (not just CE) to confirm inversion, and align with HTF structure.",
